== Historical Significance ==

In 2014, Nakayama Otsuka Kofun was Historic Site1 a National Historic Site as part of the "Yamato Kofun Cluster," alongside {{ill|Nomugi Kofun|ja|ノムギ古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nomugi Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Shimoikeyama Kofun|ja|下池山古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimoikeyama Kofun|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/40100003861|title=Yamato Kofun Cluster|publisher=Historic Site Online|accessdate=2021}}</ref>

